history.content: I did that and it was quite alright. Each course will give you a weekly homework, and 126 on top of that gives you weekly labs. I think the average person spends 10 hours per homework for each class. If you think 61C + 70 is manageable, you will probably find 170 + 126 alright in terms of workload.

How is the workload for 170 + 126?

I'm taking 70 + 61c right now and its hard but still in the manageable range. How's the workload of 170+126 compared to 70+61c?

I do want to get on the ml/ai track asap but I don't want to take such a heavy courseload that I can't suceed in both classes.
